content:
The remote connectors used to sync data to CRM Analytics have new versions. Customers who joined after August 1, 2021 use only the new connector versions, while customers before August 1 can choose when to upgrade.

Upgradable Connectors:

* Amazon Redshift Connector: The new version doesn't use Amazon S3.
* Amazon S3 Connector: The new version supports connecting to objects encrypted with customer master keys stored in AWS Key Management Service or a customer-generated key in the 256-bit AES format.
* Google BigQuery Legacy SQL Connector: BigQuery Storage Read API is now supported, which can increase throughput.
* Google BigQuery Standard SQL Connector: BigQuery Storage Read API is now supported, which can increase throughput.
* Heroku Postgres Connector
* Microsoft Azure SQL Database Connector
* Microsoft Synapse Analytics Connector
* NetSuite Connector: Update your recipes and dataflows with the new object names after upgrading.
* Salesforce External Connector
* Salesforce Contacts OAuth 2.0 Connector for Marketing Cloud Engagement: The new version makes more Marketing Cloud Engagement data accessible through expanded Data Extension support.
* Snowflake Connector
* Zendesk Connector

To upgrade, select Connect to Data on the Connect tab of the Data Manager, edit the connection, deselect Use legacy connector, fill in new properties as required, and save and test.

Manually Migrated Connectors:

* Google Analytics Core Reporting v4 Connector: The new version supports custom objects.
* Marketo Connector: The new connector version supports filtering on select objects.
* Oracle Eloqua Connector: The new version currently uses different field names, includes more objects than the legacy version, and doesn't yet support the Activity object.
* SAP HANA Connector: The new connector version supports filtering, uses different connection properties, and is JDBC-based.

Your connector upgrade strategy is based on the complexity of your sources and data. Generally, you can do a Sandbox comparison or build mirror connections, then generate sync objects that you can compare.
title: Upgrading Salesforce CRM Analytics Connectors
